article.description: — Tyson Jolly and Quinn Slazinski scored 18 points apiece as Iona defeated North Alabama 81-65 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Jolly, Slazinski lift Iona over North Alabama 81-65
article.linkText: Jolly, Slazinski lift Iona over North Alabama 81-65
article.story: KISSIMMEE, Fla. -- — Tyson Jolly and Quinn Slazinski scored 18 points apiece as Iona defeated North Alabama 81-65 on Saturday night. Nelly Junior Joseph added 17 points for the Gaels. Junior Joseph also had nine rebounds and three blocks. Dylan van Eyck had 14 points and seven rebounds for Iona (5-0), which won its fifth consecutive game to start the season. Jamari Blackmon had 11 points for the Lions (1-3). Daniel Ortiz added 11 points. Damian Forrest had eight rebounds and three blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
